    <text>
        <body>
            <pb facs="MSVIII72r"/>
            <div type="witness" subtype="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" rhyme="aabbccbbbddeeaafgffhh">
                <lg type="stanza" n="1">
                    <l><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="cursive" medium="ink"/>The bloom was on the <placeName corresp="#BOURDEAUX">Bourdeaux</placeName> grape, and ripe along the <geogName corresp="#RHINE">Rhine</geogName></l>
                    <l>And Yellow <!--"Xeres" = Spanish name for Sherry wine. Gloss needed?-->Xeres hills looked forth the clusters of the vine</l>
                    <l>The summer sunshine <unclear reason="smudged">rolled</unclear> all his force along the plain,</l>
                    <l>And the vintage of the vallies it was gathering again,</l>
                    <l>Through all the Breadth of <placeName corresp="#BURGUNDY">Burgundy</placeName> the grape was round and red,</l>
                    <l>And in festoons through all the south, was hanging overhead</l>
                    <l>Come forth, come forth, ye vintage men on <placeName corresp="#ITALY">Italy</placeName> and <placeName corresp="#SPAIN">Spain</placeName></l>
                <pb facs="MSVIII72v"/>
                    <l><space quantity="6" unit="chars"/>On <placeName corresp="#BOURDEAUX">Bourdeaux</placeName> and on <placeName corresp="#BURGUNDY">Burgundy</placeName>, the <geogName corresp="#RHINE">Rhine</geogName>, and all <placeName corresp="#CHAMPAGNE">Champagne</placeName>,</l>
                    <l>Come, gather to the gathering. Tis vintage time again.</l>
                    <l>From dawn till set of sun with festal song the vineyards rung</l>
                    <l>The spirit of the crushed red grape ran rosily along</l>
                    <l>And there was scarce a river fish but on that day could tell,</l>
                    <l>How winy were the waters of the <geogName corresp="#MEUSE">Meuse</geogName> and the <geogName corresp="#MOSELLE">Moselle</geogName></l>
                    <l>Full teemed with life the rocky sides of the impetuous <geogName corresp="#RHINE">Rhine</geogName></l>
                    <l>Oer every crag rose terraces, on each of them, the vine.</l>
                    <l>Full merrily they crushed the vines were searched on all the rivers there</l>
                    <l>They crushed the fruit with right good will&#x2014;the vintage feast</l>
                    <l>There was a cavern deep and cold, and arched oer with care,</l>
                    <l>The juice of every distant grape was safely hoarded there.</l>
                    <l>The liquid gold from <!--"Xeres" = Spanish name for Sherry wine. Gloss needed?-->Xeres came. there wanted not <placeName corresp="#BOURDEAUX">Bourdeaux</placeName></l>
                    <l>Who doubted of the right good Hock the cellarman could show.</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
